Directions & Blood Relationship Practice Set 🧭🧩
Directions Based Questions
1.

Ravi walks 10 m towards North, then turns right and walks 15 m. Then he turns right and walks 10 m. In which direction is he from the starting point?

A) North
B) East
C) South
D) West

2.

A is standing facing South. He turns 90° clockwise and then 90° anti-clockwise. Which direction is he facing now?

A) East
B) West
C) North
D) South

3.

P is to the East of Q. R is to the North of Q. In which direction is P with respect to R?

A) North-East
B) South-East
C) South-West
D) North-West

4.

Meena walks 20 m East, then 20 m South, then 20 m West. How far and in which direction is she from the starting point?

A) 20 m North
B) 20 m South
C) 40 m South
D) 0 m

5.

Karan walks 5 m North, then 12 m East. What is the shortest distance from the starting point?

A) 13 m
B) 17 m
C) 10 m
D) 7 m

6.

A man walks 15 m South, then turns left and walks 10 m, then turns left again and walks 15 m. Where is he now with respect to the starting point?

A) 10 m East
B) 10 m West
C) 15 m North
D) Starting point

7.

X is North of Y. Z is West of Y. In which direction is X with respect to Z?

A) North-West
B) North-East
C) South-East
D) South-West

8.

A person walks 25 m North, then 25 m East, then 25 m South. Where is he from the starting point?

A) 25 m East
B) 25 m West
C) 25 m North
D) Starting point

9.

If East becomes North-East and West becomes South-West, then North becomes?

A) East
B) North-West
C) South-East
D) South-West

10.

Raju is facing West. He turns 135° clockwise. Which direction is he facing?

A) North-East
B) South-West
C) North-West
D) South-East

11.

A is to the South of B. C is to the East of B. D is to the North of C. In which direction is D from A?

A) North-East
B) South-East
C) North-West
D) South-West

12.

Sita walks 10 m East, then turns right and walks 10 m, then turns left and walks 5 m. In which direction is she moving finally?

A) East
B) North
C) South
D) West

